      • getLogsForHourAsStream

        public java.io.InputStream getLogsForHourAsStream(java.util.Date date)
        Gets the logs for the hour of the given date, as a stream. This is a convenience method for getLogsForHourAsStream(date, null).
        Parameters:
        date - the date, which will be formatted as an hour time bucket.
        Returns:
        the stream containing the logs as XML. This must be closed by the client in order to release the connection.
        See Also:
        getLogsForHourAsStream(Date,String), TimeBucketUtils.forHour(Date)

        Gets the logs for the hour of the given date, as a stream. This formats the date as yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH in UTC time and supplies that as the time bucket for getLogsForTimeBucketAsStream(String).
        Parameters:
        date - the date, which will be formatted as an hour time bucket.
        Returns:
        the stream containing the logs as XML. This must be closed by the client in order to release the connection.

        public java.io.InputStream getLogsForMinuteAsStream(java.util.Date date,
                                                    java.lang.String language)
        Gets the logs for the minute of the given date, as a stream. This formats the date as yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm in UTC time and supplies that as the time bucket for getLogsForTimeBucketAsStream(String).
        Parameters:

      • getLogsForTimeBucketAsStream

        public java.io.InputStream getLogsForTimeBucketAsStream(java.lang.String timeBucket)
        Gets the logs for the given time bucket, as a stream. A time bucket can be either an hour or a minute of any day, in the form of yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH for hour or yy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm for minute. API Call: GET /audit/logs?time_bucket={timeBucket}
        Parameters:
        timeBucket - the time bucket for which to retrieve the logs.
        Returns:
        the stream containing the logs as XML. This must be closed by the client in order to release the connection.

      • getLogsForTimeBucketAsStream

        public java.io.InputStream getLogsForTimeBucketAsStream(java.lang.String timeBucket,
                                                        java.lang.String language)
        Gets the logs for the given time bucket, as a stream. A time bucket can be either an hour or a minute of any day, in the form of yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH for hour or yy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm for minute. API Call: GET /audit/logs?time_bucket={timeBucket} and language={language}
        Parameters:
        timeBucket - the time bucket for which to retrieve the logs.
        language - the language for the logs (optional).
        Returns:
        the stream containing the logs as XML. This must be closed by the client in order to release the connection.
